{"author":{"id":"ebc33c917f24c7ecdfaaeb19b9520a3686eb1ec98618bca0d867a3a5fcf9c601"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1725448256,"nonce":"AhdrNqFpOZMrmMI5Jv1B/AQq8LY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s6VT8Kw","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6301","origin":"github"},"title":"Constrain biopython dependency for deg_annotate","message":"Hi there,\n\nI found and I found an issue with the tool [Annotate DESeq2/DEXSeq output tables](https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repository?repository_id=e33c4ee81be2b1b4).\n\nWe're running a self-hosted Galaxy instance (24.1.1) on a Ubuntu system (22.04.4) using conda (24.7.1) for job execution. Galaxy creates a conda environment for this tool and I believe what's happening is with a newer Python version (3.12), biopython is updated to a version deg_annotate can't handle.\n\nThe conda environment list is as follows:\n```\nconda list \n# packages in environment at /srv/galaxy/var/dependencies/_conda/envs/mulled-v1-61ba501081daf9921383c1402c51e68d5421ca2253eaf7867e6d4de3e09b2263:\n#\n# Name                    Version                   Build  Channel\n_libgcc_mutex             0.1                 conda_forge    conda-forge\n_openmp_mutex             4.5                       2_gnu    conda-forge\nbcbiogff                  0.6.4                      py_1    bioconda\nbedtools                  2.27.0               he513fc3_4    bioconda\nbiopython                 1.83            py312h98912ed_0    conda-forge\nbzip2                     1.0.8                hd590300_5    conda-forge\nca-certificates           2024.2.2             hbcca054_0    conda-forge\nld_impl_linux-64          2.40                 hf3520f5_1    conda-forge\nlibblas                   3.9.0           22_linux64_openblas    conda-forge\nlibcblas                  3.9.0           22_linux64_openblas    conda-forge\nlibexpat                  2.6.2                h59595ed_0    conda-forge\nlibffi                    3.4.2                h7f98852_5    conda-forge\nlibgcc-ng                 13.2.0               h77fa898_7    conda-forge\nlibgfortran-ng            13.2.0               h69a702a_7    conda-forge\nlibgfortran5              13.2.0               hca663fb_7    conda-forge\nlibgomp                   13.2.0               h77fa898_7    conda-forge\nliblapack                 3.9.0           22_linux64_openblas    conda-forge\nlibnsl                    2.0.1                hd590300_0    conda-forge\nlibopenblas               0.3.27          pthreads_h413a1c8_0    conda-forge\nlibsqlite                 3.45.3               h2797004_0    conda-forge\nlibstdcxx-ng              13.2.0               hc0a3c3a_7    conda-forge\nlibuuid                   2.38.1               h0b41bf4_0    conda-forge\nlibxcrypt                 4.4.36               hd590300_1    conda-forge\nlibzlib                   1.2.13               h4ab18f5_6    conda-forge\nncurses                   6.5                  h59595ed_0    conda-forge\nnumpy                     1.26.4          py312heda63a1_0    conda-forge\nopenssl                   3.3.0                h4ab18f5_3    conda-forge\npip                       24.0               pyhd8ed1ab_0    conda-forge\npython                    3.12.3          hab00c5b_0_cpython    conda-forge\npython_abi                3.12                    4_cp312    conda-forge\nreadline                  8.2                  h8228510_1    conda-forge\nsetuptools                70.0.0             pyhd8ed1ab_0    conda-forge\nsix                       1.16.0             pyh6c4a22f_0    conda-forge\ntk                        8.6.13          noxft_h4845f30_101    conda-forge\ntzdata                    2024a                h0c530f3_0    conda-forge\nwheel                     0.43.0             pyhd8ed1ab_1    conda-forge\nxz                        5.2.6                h166bdaf_0    conda-forge\nzlib                      1.2.13               h4ab18f5_6    conda-forge\n```\n\nThe resulting error of the jobs are:\n```\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/srv/galaxy/var/shed_tools/toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repos/iuc/deg_annotate/e98d4ab5b5bc/deg_annotate/deg_annotate.py\", line 5, in \u003cmodule\u003e\n    from BCBio import GFF\n  File \"/srv/galaxy/var/dependencies/_conda/envs/mulled-v1-61ba501081daf9921383c1402c51e68d5421ca2253eaf7867e6d4de3e09b2263/lib/python3.12/site-packages/bcbio_gff-0.6.4-py2.7.egg/BCBio/GFF/__init__.py\", line 3, in \u003cmodule\u003e\n  File \"/srv/galaxy/var/dependencies/_conda/envs/mulled-v1-61ba501081daf9921383c1402c51e68d5421ca2253eaf7867e6d4de3e09b2263/lib/python3.12/site-packages/bcbio_gff-0.6.4-py2.7.egg/BCBio/GFF/GFFParser.py\", line 32, in \u003cmodule\u003e\nImportError: cannot import name 'UnknownSeq' from 'Bio.Seq' (/srv/galaxy/var/dependencies/_conda/envs/mulled-v1-61ba501081daf9921383c1402c51e68d5421ca2253eaf7867e6d4de3e09b2263/lib/python3.12/site-packages/Bio/Seq.py)\n```\n\nChecking the [changelog of biopython](https://github.com/biopython/biopython/blob/master/NEWS.rst#3-june-2021-biopython-179), I can see that 'UnknownSeq' has been deprecated. So what I did to fix this, is to pin the biopython version to 1.78 in the according conda environment.\n\nThe permanent and future proof fix would be to pin biopython to said version. Change\n\nhttps://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/731f04b7f59bd92cc68ad1c7565ae35960e75645/tools/deg_annotate/deg_annotate.xml#L3-L6\n\nto this:\n\n```\n \u003crequirements\u003e \n     \u003crequirement type=\"package\" version=\"2.27.0\"\u003ebedtools\u003c/requirement\u003e \n     \u003crequirement type=\"package\" version=\"0.6.4\"\u003ebcbiogff\u003c/requirement\u003e \n     \u003crequirement type=\"package\" version=\"1.78\"\u003ebiopython\u003c/requirement\u003e \n \u003c/requirements\u003e \n```\n\nKeep up the good work!","files":null}]}